“Is it perchance that sort of thing the unbelievers have of late conveyed  
from beyond the great seas, which, when boiled in oil,  
and with an onion and salt thereto added, doth--”

E’en flog the dogs, and drub them sounder!
The mair they skirl, the closer rounder;
And still, amang the hands, a brisker
O’ something stout;
It gars an owthor’s pulse beat faster,
And helps his wit.

